article.description: Jimmy Seewald tossed two TD passes to Jarrett Morgan, Frank Cartine rushed for 114 yards and a score, and Valparaiso hung for a 42-39 victory over Jacksonville on Saturday.
article.headline: Valpo survives Jacksonville's late flurry, wins 42-39
article.linkText: Valpo survives Jacksonville's late flurry, wins 42-39
article.story: VALPARAISO, Ind. -- Jimmy Seewald tossed two TD passes to Jarrett Morgan, Frank Cartine rushed for 114 yards and a score, and Valparaiso hung for a 42-39 victory over Jacksonville on Saturday. Valparaiso (4-7, 3-5 Pioneer) led 42-24 after three quarters, but the Crusaders didn't manage a first down in the final period. Jacksonville cut it to 42-32 on Will Montgomery's 3-yard run with 8:55 to play. Jacksonville (4-5, 3-3) forced a three-and-out but turned it over on downs at Valpo's 9-yard line with 6:26 left, opting not for the field goal that would have made it a one-score game. The Dolphins got the ball back with 3:33 left and needed just 1:05 to go 59 yards. Brian Burnett capped the drive with a 23-yard TD reception from Rylan Wells to make the score 42-39. Seewald ran for a 47-yard loss on the game's final play to allow the clock to expire. Valparaiso led 28-3 after Catrine's 72-yard run with 2:23 left in the first quarter. The Crusaders were outgained 551-367.
